## Data Licensing

### Government Data Sources
Data extracted from U.S. Government sources (including the U.S. Energy Information 
Administration) is in the public domain and not subject to copyright restrictions 
within the United States.

### Processed Data and Enhancements
All processing, analysis, cross-reference mapping, and structural enhancements 
added to the original government data are licensed under the MIT License above.

### Attribution Requirements
When using this data, please provide appropriate attribution:

"Energy industry taxonomy data originally sourced from the U.S. Energy Information 
Administration (EIA). Processing and enhancements by the Industry Taxonomies project, 
licensed under MIT License."

### Commercial Use
Commercial use is permitted under the MIT License. No additional permissions are 
required for commercial applications, though attribution is appreciated.

### Derivative Works
You are free to create derivative works, modifications, and enhancements. We 
encourage contributions back to the main repository to benefit the entire community.

### International Use
While U.S. Government data is public domain within the United States, users in 
other jurisdictions should verify local copyright and usage requirements.

For questions about licensing, please contact the project maintainers or open 
an issue in the GitHub repository.

